  "body": "As a user, I want to stay signed in to sites when I close and reopen the Status browser.\r\n\r\nCurrently, the browser clears all data upon exiting, but it would be nice to select websites that are allowed to store data. This is useful so I don't have to sign into GitHub every single time I reopen the Status app.\r\n\r\n### Example implementations\r\nThis could be done like the \"Fire\" button on the DuckDuckGo mobile apps, where you can choose what sites are allowed to store data, and get rid of everything else.",
